title: 820-01987 with low PP3V3_G3H
message:
Board came in dead, drawing just 5V and draws 20V with battery collected only. Checked for PP3V3_G3H, it was 1V

Checked U7650, pin 23 12V is present
And none of the enable signals were present

Is the machine recognized in DFU?

title: 820-01987 with low PP3V3_G3H
message:
Machine cannot enter DFU without AWAKE and SLPS2R voltages.
You may have a problem with U7800.
Check PMIC LDOs in page 71.
Be sure R7900 is good.

title: 820-01987 with low PP3V3_G3H
message:
Are you sure R7900 is good?
Check voltage on pin 2.

If OK, then change U7800.
First be sure no short on its LDOs...

title: 820-01987 with low PP3V3_G3H
message:
Yeah R7900 is a 0ohm resistor and it has a 3.3V on both sides, checked all LDO's resistance using diode mode, there was no short.
Pls what's the meaning of LDO....

title: 820-01987 with low PP3V3_G3H
message:
Low Drop Output.
You can see the notation in the name of some power rails.
